gnd cover — group the citation graph by scanned file.

Usage:  gnd cover [PATH] [--format text|json]

PATH defaults to `.`. The command runs the same scan as `check` and `refs`,
then prints one file record with the citations found in that file.

Options:
  --format text|json   text (default) groups citations by file; json emits one record per file.

Exit:  0 scan succeeded · 2 unreadable tree, incomplete scan, or CLI error.

Examples:
  gnd cover src/                # source files and their spec citations
  gnd cover --format json       # machine-readable coverage index
